weewx-wh23xx
Copyright 2016 Matthew Wall
License: GPLv3

This is a weewx driver for Fine Offset WH23xx hardware.  These stations are
commonly available as Tycon TP2700 and Froggit WH4000 weather stations.

Installation

0) install weewx, select 'Simulator' driver

http://weewx.com/docs/usersguide.htm#installing

1) download the driver

wget -O weewx-wh23xx.zip https://github.com/matthewwall/weewx-wh23xx/archive/master.zip

2) install the driver

sudo wee_extension --install weewx-wh23xx.zip

3) configure the driver

sudo wee_config --reconfigure

4) start weewx

sudo /etc/init.d/weewx start


in kurzform:
1. Type the following in a terminal window:
sudo gedit /etc/modprobe.d/usb-core-options
2. Add the following line to the usb-core-options file:
options usbcore autosuspend=-1
3. Save your changes, and then type the following in a terminal window:
sudo update-initramfs -u
4. Shutdown and power on your computer. (Don't use the restart option)

seitdem funktioniert usb bei mir einwandfrei!!
